---
import BaseHead from "../components/BaseHead.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import { SITE_TITLE } from "../consts";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead
      title={`Projects | ${SITE_TITLE}`}
      description="A collection of the projects, experiments and ideas I’m building alongside my homelab."
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />

    <main class="page">
      <section class="hero">
        <p class="eyebrow">What I'm building</p>
        <h1>Projects</h1>
        <p class="intro">
          These are the projects, experiments and ideas I’m working on outside of the
          day-to-day running of my homelab. Some are active, some are early, and some
          are still taking shape.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="grid">
        <article class="card">
          <h2>Retro Refresh</h2>
          <p>
            A project focused on refurbishing and upgrading retro tech, starting with
            iPods and expanding into other devices over time.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>iPod Classic flash and battery upgrades</li>
            <li>Testing parts before selling anything</li>
            <li>Building a repeatable and reliable workflow</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <h2>Fitrics</h2>
          <p>
            A project to analyse fitness data from FIT files and turn it into something
            more useful and easier to understand.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Processing activity data</li>
            <li>Exploring visualisations and trends</li>
            <li>Building something I would genuinely use myself</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <h2>This site</h2>
          <p>
            AdamBray.me is a project in its own right. It’s where I document what I’m
            building, what’s working, and what I’ve learned along the way.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Writing about my homelab and systems</li>
            <li>Creating a clear public home for projects</li>
            <li>Keeping things simple and personal</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <h2>Future ideas</h2>
          <p>
            Not everything needs to be fully formed before it earns a place here.
            These are the areas I want to explore next.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Small internal tools for my own use</li>
            <li>Better backup and workflow tooling</li>
            <li>Automations that solve real problems at home</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section class="philosophy">
        <h2>How I think about projects</h2>
        <p>
          I’m not interested in building things just for the sake of it. The projects
          here are all tied to something practical, something I want to improve, or
          something I want to understand properly.
        </p>
      </section>
    </main>

    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  .page {
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 3rem 1.5rem 5rem;
  }

  .hero {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    opacity: 0.65;
  }

  h1 {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 4.2vw, 3.2rem);
    line-height: 1.1;
  }

  .intro {
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 60ch;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    opacity: 0.9;
  }

  .grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .card {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(128, 128, 128, 0.18);
    border-radius: 18px;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
    transition: transform 0.15s ease, border-color 0.15s ease;
  }

  .card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    border-color: rgba(128, 128, 128, 0.3);
  }

  .card h2 {
    margin: 0 0 0.9rem;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
  }

  .card p,
  .card li {
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .card p {
    margin: 0 0 0.9rem;
  }

  .card p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .card ul {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
  }

  .card li + li {
    margin-top: 0.45rem;
  }

  .philosophy {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(128, 128, 128, 0.15);
  }

  .philosophy h2 {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
  }

  .philosophy p {
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.75;
    opacity: 0.9;
  }

  @media (max-width: 800px) {
    .page {
      padding: 2rem 1.25rem 4rem;
    }

    .grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .intro {
      font-size: 1.05rem;
    }
  }
</style>
